result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jacob Jermaine Johnson in court with attorney Michael V Fuentes.  Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defense counsel challenges probable cause to Counts 1 & 2 and moves to dismiss. State objects for reasons set forth in the record.
Court finds probable cause and DENIES defense motion to dismiss. Defense counsel requests final pre trial and jury trial.
Case adjourned for final pretrial and for jury trial in Branch 1.
  Final pre-trial scheduled for December 19, 2022 at 09:00 am.  Jury trial scheduled for January 3, 2023 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jacob Jermaine Johnson in court.  
Constatine Siapkaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Attorney Michael Fuentes appeared as a Friend of the Court.
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Hearing held via Zoom.  Matter set for pretrial conference.  Counsel has not been appointed yet, but Atty. Fuentes will take this case and requests a status date.  Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  Status conference scheduled for August 11, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON 06-09-2022. IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Defendant Jacob Jermaine Johnson in court.  John J Rejowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 1.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 06/07/2022@1p
